WEBVTT

1
00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:51.030
It's been near six years

2
00:01:51.110 --> 00:01:53.740
since I last saw

3
00:01:51.110 --> 00:01:53.740
my lord husband. maester.

4
00:01:54.380 --> 00:01:57.570
I must know... will he live?

5
00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:01.310
He led his sailors

6
00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:01.310
into an ambush.

7
00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:03.780
A ship made to look

8
00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:03.780
as if it were abandoned.

9
00:02:05.220 --> 00:02:08.750
In the fighting. his neck was slashed

10
00:02:05.220 --> 00:02:08.750
by a corsair's dagger.

11
00:02:09.460 --> 00:02:12.220
He fell overboard into the sea.

12
00:02:12.290 --> 00:02:14.160
The wound was severe.

13
00:02:14.260 --> 00:02:15.990
Much blood was lost.

14
00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:19.070
But the greater concern

15
00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:19.070
is the fever that followed.

16
00:02:19.130 --> 00:02:22.300
The ship's maester said

17
00:02:19.130 --> 00:02:22.300
he burns from within.

18
00:02:35.450 --> 00:02:37.250
The ravens came in from?

19
00:02:37.320 --> 00:02:38.950
Evenfall. Princess.

20
00:02:40.860 --> 00:02:42.480
So they arrive in three days.

21
00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:47.850
Let all be made ready to receive him.

22
00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:47.850
Maester Kelvyn.

23
00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:56.700
- The Sea Snake is strong.

24
00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:56.700
Hmm.

25
00:02:56.810 --> 00:02:57.970
No doubt.

26
00:02:58.510 --> 00:03:02.540
And yet. I have seen blood fever

27
00:02:58.510 --> 00:03:02.540
overcome men half his age.

28
00:03:02.640 --> 00:03:05.770
I will not suffer the talk

29
00:03:02.640 --> 00:03:05.770
of crows in my house. Vaemond.

30
00:03:05.850 --> 00:03:07.540
I love my brother...

31
00:03:08.450 --> 00:03:10.440
but we must be honest with ourselves.

32
00:03:11.190 --> 00:03:13.350
We may greet his ship to find him gone.

33
00:03:13.460 --> 00:03:15.890
And who will take the Driftwood Throne?

34
00:03:15.990 --> 00:03:17.790
My grandmother seems

35
00:03:15.990 --> 00:03:17.790
quite comfortable here.

36
00:03:17.860 --> 00:03:20.800
She presides only in the absence

37
00:03:17.860 --> 00:03:20.800
of her husband.

38
00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:24.500
On his death. the seat passes.

39
00:03:24.570 --> 00:03:25.800
To Lucerys Velaryon.

40
00:03:25.870 --> 00:03:27.530
As is my lord husband's desire.

41
00:03:27.640 --> 00:03:31.000
I am the Sea Snake's own blood.

42
00:03:31.070 --> 00:03:33.570
the closest kin he has left.

43
00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.140
Be careful. good-brother.

44
00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:37.740
One could take your words for treason.

45
00:03:46.590 --> 00:03:49.250
I speak the truth. Rhaenys.

46
00:03:50.760 --> 00:03:52.090
And you know it.

47
00:03:53.360 --> 00:03:55.060
The matter has been decided.

48
00:03:55.160 --> 00:03:56.890
By a man whose ambition

49
00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:00.730
has brought down on us

50
00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:00.730
calamity after calamity.

51
00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:03.830
My brother cares only

52
00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:03.830
for the history books.

53
00:04:06.210 --> 00:04:08.400
But what of the Velaryon line?

54
00:04:08.510 --> 00:04:11.040
Is it to be snuffed out.

55
00:04:11.110 --> 00:04:13.880
supplanted by the pups of House Strong?

56
00:04:14.350 --> 00:04:17.880
Driftmark is mine by all rights.

57
00:04:17.950 --> 00:04:19.920
And while I should like your support.

58
00:04:20.020 --> 00:04:23.010
I do not need it.

59
00:04:25.230 --> 00:04:26.560
The winds have shifted.

60
00:04:28.060 --> 00:04:32.020
The Crown has good reason

61
00:04:28.060 --> 00:04:32.020
to take my side.

62
00:04:32.430 --> 00:04:35.200
My cousin the King

63
00:04:32.430 --> 00:04:35.200
would have your tongue for this.

64
00:04:35.270 --> 00:04:40.270
But it's not a king who sits

65
00:04:35.270 --> 00:04:40.270
the Iron Throne these days. good-sister.

66
00:04:41.210 --> 00:04:42.910
It's a queen.

67
00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:04.550
The Conqueror and

68
00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:04.550
his sisters sailed with a great army.

69
00:07:11.060 --> 00:07:13.690
And landed

70
00:07:11.060 --> 00:07:13.690
at the Blackwater Rush.

71
00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:22.470
At the end?

72
00:07:22.570 --> 00:07:23.900
- The mouth.

73
00:07:22.570 --> 00:07:23.900
- Mouth!

74
00:07:23.970 --> 00:07:26.200
Oh. come on. Jace. you knew that.

75
00:07:34.920 --> 00:07:35.910
Come on. Jace.

76
00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:39.480
- Perhaps that's enough for this morning.

77
00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:39.480
- No. no. I want to keep going.

78
00:07:41.060 --> 00:07:42.120
Maester.

79
00:07:45.490 --> 00:07:48.930
Aegon... ordered

80
00:07:45.490 --> 00:07:48.930
that the trees should be...

81
00:07:49.830 --> 00:07:51.770
- ...killed.

82
00:07:49.830 --> 00:07:51.770
Felled.

83
00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:53.270
It is a related word.

84
00:07:53.740 --> 00:07:55.970
I don't expect you to learn

85
00:07:53.740 --> 00:07:55.970
High Valyrian in a day. Jace.

86
00:07:56.070 --> 00:07:59.340
A king should honor

87
00:07:56.070 --> 00:07:59.340
the traditions of his forbears.

88
00:07:59.440 --> 00:08:02.140
Well... unless you're planning

89
00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:05.240
to depose your own mother.

90
00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:05.240
you have plenty of time to study.

91
00:08:13.620 --> 00:08:14.820
Leave us.

92
00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:18.620
Joffrey... come.

93
00:08:39.450 --> 00:08:42.040
He means to call into question

94
00:08:39.450 --> 00:08:42.040
Luke's legitimacy.

95
00:08:43.620 --> 00:08:45.450
And by extension. Jace.

96
00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:47.650
and by extension.

97
00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:47.650
my own claim to the throne.

98
00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:50.950
Vaemond cares only about Driftmark

99
00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:50.950
and the Velaryon line.

100
00:08:51.860 --> 00:08:53.490
Not about our politics.

101
00:08:54.330 --> 00:08:56.130
Has he made common cause

102
00:08:54.330 --> 00:08:56.130
with Otto Hightower yet?

103
00:08:56.200 --> 00:08:58.330
Mmm. This is what I fear.

104
00:08:58.400 --> 00:09:00.390
Rhaenys has flown to court.

105
00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:02.130
Surely. she cannot

106
00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:02.130
be planning to back him.

107
00:09:02.200 --> 00:09:04.230
No. Whatever disagreements

108
00:09:02.200 --> 00:09:04.230
we may have had.

109
00:09:04.340 --> 00:09:05.670
she's not cruel...

110
00:09:06.310 --> 00:09:09.140
- or stupid enough to do that.

111
00:09:06.310 --> 00:09:09.140
- Disagreements?

112
00:09:09.210 --> 00:09:12.310
She believes we had her son killed

113
00:09:09.210 --> 00:09:12.310
so that we might marry.

114
00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:16.180
Yes... and yet.

115
00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:16.180
she's taken Baela to ward.

116
00:09:16.250 --> 00:09:18.910
Yes. It is Laena's memory she honors.

117
00:09:16.250 --> 00:09:18.910
She has no love for us.

118
00:09:20.820 --> 00:09:23.050
Has the vipers' venom spread so far?

119
00:09:23.160 --> 00:09:25.560
Those vipers rule in my father's name.

120
00:09:26.360 --> 00:09:27.990
And my father...

121
00:09:34.770 --> 00:09:36.260
What choice do I have?

122
00:09:42.910 --> 00:09:44.170
To King's Landing. then.

123
00:10:25.650 --> 00:10:28.820
All hail Rhaenyra

124
00:10:25.650 --> 00:10:28.820
of House Targaryen.

125
00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:31.390
Princess of Dragonstone

126
00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:31.390
and heir to the Iron Throne

127
00:10:31.460 --> 00:10:35.090
and her royal consort.

128
00:10:31.460 --> 00:10:35.090
Prince Daemon Targaryen.

129
00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:10.990
Welcome back. Princess.

130
00:11:11.970 --> 00:11:12.960
Lord Caswell.

131
00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:25.680
I would say it's nice to be home.

132
00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:25.680
but I scarcely recognize it.

133
00:11:26.610 --> 00:11:27.480
Hmm.

134
00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:36.490
We have continued

135
00:11:31.720 --> 00:11:36.490
to enjoy improved customs duties

136
00:11:36.560 --> 00:11:39.490
since the settling of the Stepstones.

137
00:11:39.560 --> 00:11:42.290
And the extent to which we exploit those

138
00:11:42.360 --> 00:11:46.530
is contingent on

139
00:11:42.360 --> 00:11:46.530
the harbor master's receipts.

140
00:11:46.900 --> 00:11:48.530
Of which. um.

141
00:11:48.640 --> 00:11:51.970
uh. the septons have requested

142
00:11:52.040 --> 00:11:54.240
half that again for a bronze bust

143
00:11:54.340 --> 00:11:55.810
they wish to commission

144
00:11:55.880 --> 00:11:57.870
- for the Festival of the Mother...

145
00:11:57.980 --> 00:11:59.310
...which I would not recommend.

146
00:11:59.380 --> 00:12:02.320
Thank you for that exhaustive

147
00:11:59.380 --> 00:12:02.320
accounting. Lord Beesbury.

148
00:12:02.380 --> 00:12:03.580
I remind you--

149
00:12:11.260 --> 00:12:13.160
Your guests have arrived. Your Grace.

150
00:12:13.230 --> 00:12:15.930
I trust they've been welcomed

151
00:12:13.230 --> 00:12:15.930
as befits their station.

152
00:12:16.030 --> 00:12:17.590
As you instructed.

153
00:12:16.030 --> 00:12:17.590
Lord Hand.

154
00:12:19.770 --> 00:12:23.730
It was my understanding Lord Corlys

155
00:12:19.770 --> 00:12:23.730
wished for his grandson Lucerys

156
00:12:23.840 --> 00:12:25.570
to succeed him as Lord of the Tides.

157
00:12:25.670 --> 00:12:28.870
The boy has been raised most of his life

158
00:12:25.670 --> 00:12:28.870
away from Driftmark.

159
00:12:29.710 --> 00:12:33.080
He can fly a dragon. yes.

160
00:12:29.710 --> 00:12:33.080
but can he command a fleet?

161
00:12:33.180 --> 00:12:35.510
Ability does not alter his claim.

162
00:12:35.580 --> 00:12:38.520
The Sea Snake has never

163
00:12:35.580 --> 00:12:38.520
formally named him as heir.

164
00:12:38.590 --> 00:12:40.020
if it comes to that.

165
00:12:40.090 --> 00:12:42.460
The Crown must choose

166
00:12:40.090 --> 00:12:42.460
what is best for the realm.

167
00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:45.290
He is Laenor's son.

168
00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:45.290
What grounds could there be--

169
00:12:45.390 --> 00:12:47.420
What indeed. Lord Beesbury.

170
00:12:47.530 --> 00:12:49.190
What indeed.

171
00:12:50.300 --> 00:12:51.770
We shall hear

172
00:12:50.300 --> 00:12:51.770
Princess Rhaenyra's petition.

173
00:12:51.870 --> 00:12:53.890
along with those of the other claimants

174
00:12:51.870 --> 00:12:53.890
on the morrow.

175
00:12:54.040 --> 00:12:56.270
- I do beg your pardon. my lords.

176
00:12:56.940 --> 00:12:58.410
I must greet our guests.

177
00:13:03.810 --> 00:13:06.710
Shall we levy a tax

178
00:13:03.810 --> 00:13:06.710
on the sale of new wool?

179
00:13:06.780 --> 00:13:08.480
Your Grace...

180
00:13:08.580 --> 00:13:10.610
a matter has arisen

181
00:13:08.580 --> 00:13:10.610
that requires your attention.

182
00:13:10.720 --> 00:13:12.810
Whatever it is. Ser Arryk.

183
00:13:10.720 --> 00:13:12.810
it'll need to wait.

184
00:13:12.920 --> 00:13:16.620
- I'm Erryk. Your Grace.

185
00:13:12.920 --> 00:13:16.620
- Of course. My apologies. ser.

186
00:13:16.720 --> 00:13:18.320
It's about the Prince.

187
00:13:18.430 --> 00:13:20.830
There's been a delicate situation

188
00:13:18.430 --> 00:13:20.830
in his apartments.

189
00:13:52.990 --> 00:13:53.980
Father?

190
00:14:19.690 --> 00:14:22.450
- Who goes there?

191
00:14:19.690 --> 00:14:22.450
Father.

192
00:14:23.890 --> 00:14:26.120
It's me. my king.

193
00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:28.490
Rhaenyra.

194
00:14:36.800 --> 00:14:38.200
I'm here with Daemon.

195
00:14:39.710 --> 00:14:40.970
Daemon?

196
00:14:41.540 --> 00:14:42.740
Daemon?

197
00:14:45.250 --> 00:14:46.540
Daemon.

198
00:14:49.880 --> 00:14:51.320
Help me up.

199
00:14:57.690 --> 00:14:58.920
Oh...

200
00:15:08.600 --> 00:15:10.230
It has been so long.

201
00:15:16.280 --> 00:15:19.440
The Sea Snake has taken a grave wound

202
00:15:16.280 --> 00:15:19.440
in battle in the Stepstones.

203
00:15:19.880 --> 00:15:23.410
When?

204
00:15:23.520 --> 00:15:25.950
We won that war years ago.

205
00:15:26.050 --> 00:15:27.080
No.

206
00:15:28.420 --> 00:15:30.090
The Triarchy is resurgent.

207
00:15:31.530 --> 00:15:32.890
The fighting is anew.

208
00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:38.200
There's... There is a petition to decide

209
00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:38.200
upon the succession of Driftmark

210
00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:40.260
and the heir to the Driftwood Throne.

211
00:15:43.140 --> 00:15:44.130
Petitions?

212
00:15:46.970 --> 00:15:51.070
Alicent and Otto...

213
00:15:46.970 --> 00:15:51.070
they see to all that business now.

214
00:15:51.150 --> 00:15:53.240
No. brother. listen to me.

215
00:15:54.120 --> 00:15:56.550
You are to affirm

216
00:15:54.120 --> 00:15:56.550
your position for Lucerys...

217
00:15:57.590 --> 00:15:59.580
to be Corlys Velaryon's successor.

218
00:16:02.160 --> 00:16:04.130
Has something happened

219
00:16:02.160 --> 00:16:04.130
to Lord Corlys?

220
00:16:06.930 --> 00:16:08.660
Father...

221
00:16:08.760 --> 00:16:11.060
there's someone we wish

222
00:16:08.760 --> 00:16:11.060
to introduce you to.

223
00:16:29.350 --> 00:16:30.820
Daemon.

224
00:16:32.820 --> 00:16:33.810
Brother.

225
00:16:36.790 --> 00:16:38.190
Who is that?

226
00:16:40.030 --> 00:16:41.020
Father...

227
00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:44.830
this is Aegon.

228
00:16:46.300 --> 00:16:47.290
Aegon.

229
00:16:48.600 --> 00:16:51.160
And this... is Viserys.

230
00:16:55.280 --> 00:16:56.710
Viserys.

231
00:17:01.350 --> 00:17:04.180
Now that is a name fit for a king.

232
00:17:08.860 --> 00:17:10.380
Oh...

233
00:17:12.690 --> 00:17:15.460
Oh. oh...

234
00:17:15.530 --> 00:17:16.660
I'm sorry.

235
00:17:17.730 --> 00:17:20.330
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

236
00:17:21.640 --> 00:17:22.660
I'm so--

237
00:17:25.970 --> 00:17:28.700
I'm sorry. I'm sor--

238
00:17:28.810 --> 00:17:29.970
Please.

239
00:17:31.410 --> 00:17:35.010
- My tea. My tea.

240
00:17:31.410 --> 00:17:35.010
- What tea? This?

241
00:17:35.080 --> 00:17:36.910
Yes. Yes.

242
00:17:38.890 --> 00:17:40.080
Yes.

243
00:17:46.690 --> 00:17:47.920
Ah!

244
00:18:08.850 --> 00:18:11.280
I brought her here immediately.

245
00:18:11.390 --> 00:18:12.850
She's seen no one else. Your Grace.

246
00:18:18.390 --> 00:18:19.380
Come here. sweetling.

247
00:18:30.240 --> 00:18:31.210
Tell me your name.

248
00:18:34.580 --> 00:18:36.540
It's Dyana. Your Grace.

249
00:18:38.980 --> 00:18:40.110
If it please you.

250
00:18:41.920 --> 00:18:44.750
Dyana. What a pretty name.

251
00:18:48.090 --> 00:18:50.560
I understand you've found

252
00:18:48.090 --> 00:18:50.560
yourself in some trouble.

253
00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:55.630
I was fetching the Prince his wine.

254
00:18:55.730 --> 00:18:59.430
and I put it on his table.

255
00:18:55.730 --> 00:18:59.430
and when I turned--

256
00:19:00.600 --> 00:19:01.730
I didn't see him.

257
00:19:03.270 --> 00:19:05.470
I asked him to stop. Your Grace.

258
00:19:05.570 --> 00:19:07.840
I did. truly...

259
00:19:08.440 --> 00:19:09.770
you must believe me.

260
00:19:24.330 --> 00:19:25.760
Thank you for telling me. Dyana.

261
00:19:31.500 --> 00:19:32.760
I know it wasn't your fault.

262
00:19:35.870 --> 00:19:36.860
I believe you.

263
00:19:37.810 --> 00:19:38.930
You do?

264
00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:41.630
I do.

265
00:19:44.810 --> 00:19:46.180
But what I worry about...

266
00:19:48.020 --> 00:19:49.310
is what others might believe.

267
00:19:52.050 --> 00:19:53.540
You were alone with the Prince.

268
00:19:52.050 --> 00:19:53.540
were you not?

269
00:19:54.620 --> 00:19:56.890
Yes. I--

270
00:19:56.990 --> 00:19:59.190
And no one else saw what happened

271
00:19:56.990 --> 00:19:59.190
between the two of you.

272
00:20:00.460 --> 00:20:02.730
If anyone else were to hear about this--

273
00:20:02.830 --> 00:20:03.990
I haven't told anyone.

274
00:20:04.070 --> 00:20:06.560
You told Ser Erryk

275
00:20:04.070 --> 00:20:06.560
and Talya and now me.

276
00:20:07.870 --> 00:20:09.230
And though I believe

277
00:20:07.870 --> 00:20:09.230
you are not to blame.

278
00:20:09.340 --> 00:20:10.740
others might not be so trusting.

279
00:20:12.670 --> 00:20:15.300
They might think you were trying

280
00:20:12.670 --> 00:20:15.300
to besmirch the Prince. or worse...

281
00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:17.470
that you're the sort of girl

282
00:20:17.550 --> 00:20:19.480
that might have enticed him

283
00:20:17.550 --> 00:20:19.480
in the first place.

284
00:20:21.420 --> 00:20:22.880
And you know what happens

285
00:20:21.420 --> 00:20:22.880
to girls like that.

286
00:20:25.520 --> 00:20:29.980
I wouldn't dream of breathing

287
00:20:25.520 --> 00:20:29.980
another word to anyone. Your Grace.

288
00:20:31.390 --> 00:20:33.380
I swear it on my life.

289
00:20:40.870 --> 00:20:41.860
I know you won't.

290
00:20:55.380 --> 00:20:56.370
For your troubles.

